{{wikipedia|lang=ja|カササギ}}
{{ja-kanjitab|かささぎ|yomi=k}}
Likely from {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=かささき|-}}.

Derivation {{unk|ja|nocap=y}}.
* May be derived from Proto-Altaic, as seen in {{cog|ko|까치|tr=kkachi||[[magpie]]}} and {{cog|tr|saksağan||[[magpie]]}}, all derived from [[onomatopoeia]]. This is problematic because there is little evidence of differing elisions of ''k-'' and ''s-'' in the language family.
* Alternatively, a compound of {{m|ja|カラ|tr=kara||[[caw]]|pos=onomatopoeia, seen in {{m|ja|烏|tr=karasu||[[crow]]}}}} + {{m|ja|鷦鷯|tr=sasagi||[[wren]]|pos=obsolete}}.

{{rfv-etymology|ja}}

{{ja-noun|かささぎ|カササギ}}

# a [[Eurasian magpie]] (''[[Pica pica]]'')
#* '''1205''', ''{{w|Shin Kokin Wakashū}}'' (book 5 poem 522), text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/shinkokinshu/Ano05Sh.html#522 here]
#*: {{ja-usex|'''かささぎ'''の[[雲の梯|雲のかけはし]][[秋]]%[[暮れる|暮れて]][[夜半]]には[[霜]]や[[冴え渡る|さえわたる]]らむ|'''かささぎ''' の くも の かけはし あき% くれ て よは に は しも や さえ-わたるらむ|rom='''kasasagi''' no kumo no kakehashi aki kurete yowa ni wa shimo ya sae-wataruran|To the bridge of clouds over-spanned by '''magpie''' wings comes autumn's close: for at midnight the frost spreads a chill throughout the sky.<ref>{{cite-book|1991|Steven D. Carter|Traditional Japanese Poetry: An Anthology|edition=illustrated|publisher=Stanford University Press|isbn=0-8047-2212-9|page=186}}</ref>|sort=かささき}}
#: '''1205''', ''{{w|Shin Kokin Wakashū}}'' (book 6 poem 620), text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/shinkokinshu/Ano06Sh.html#620 here] (also ''{{w|Ogura Hyakunin Isshu|Hyakunin Isshu}}'', poem 6)
#:: {{ja-usex|'''かささぎ'''の[[鵲の橋|渡せる橋]]に[[置く|おく]]霜の[[白い|白き]]を[[見る|見れ]]ば[[夜]]ぞ[[更ける|ふけ]]にける|'''かささぎ''' の わたせる はし に おく しも の しろき を みれば よ ぞ ふけ に ける|When I see the whiteness of the frost that lies on the bridge the '''magpies''' spread, then do I know, indeed, that the night has deepened.<ref>{{cite-book|1996|Joshua S. Mostow|Pictures of the Heart: The Hyakunin Isshu in Word and Image|edition=illustrated|publisher=University of Hawaii Press|isbn=0-8248-1705-2|page=158}}</ref>|sort=かささき}}
# {{lb|ja|archaic|possibly|_|obsolete|sort=}} a kind of [[heron]], now likely referred to as {{m|ja|蒼鷺|tr=aosagi||[[grey heron]]}}
